Before Kunark came out, I had a 49 shaman. His defense was quite pathetic, about 600ish armor class, though he had capped weapon skill (2h blunt, there were no spears then).<br>
Anyhoo, I used to take bets that I can beat level 50 warriors toe to toe without pet, nukes, blinds, or DoTs. Worked like a charm, I usually finished with 100% hp. It went like this: HP/str/sta/regen/MR/haste buff on the shaman, Togor the warrior, hit Rage, and go. Sure, Rage drained your mana, but it also gave you insane regen. Stacked with chloro I think it was somewhere in vicinity of 50 hp/tick. <br>
By the way, shaman did NOT have any haste items, which would have helped dramatically. If anyone remembers, it would put him at cap haste then.<br>
<br>
I repeated this experiment after Kunark came out and warriors got some obscene weapons and armor. At 52 against a fairly well equipped warrior it still worked, although at that time I did have a haste item.<br>
<br>
So. Reasons shamans can tank:<br>
1. slow<br>
2. slow<br>
3. various regens<br>
4. armor class<br>
<br>
Unfortunately mages have none of the 4 (well, regen to a degree), so it's a bit tougher. On the other hand, mage pets do more damage than shaman pet + shaman melee, so it's all good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=322344>Xirinia Gusl'ar</a>, 51 bard of Povar, <a href=http://www.freedomguard.org>Freedom Guard</a>
